OL,3,CSand collected from D-Day beach
OL,4,Creturned by grandson in 80-year promise
OL,6,FA man has fulfilled a promise to his
OL,7,Fgrandfather to return sand to the D-
OL,8,FDay beach he was sent to gathered for
OL,9,Fgood luck as the invasion began.
OL,11,FGilbert Jones, who served with the 5th
OL,12,FBerkshire Regiment, was one of 21,000
OL,13,Fmen who landed on Juno Beach on 6 June
OL,14,F1944.
OL,16,FAs he set foot on land Gilbert, from ,
OL,17,Fgrabbed a handful of sand, saving it
OL,18,Fin his mess tin for luck and carrying
OL,19,Fit around for the rest of the war.
