OL,3,CSand collected from D-Day beach
OL,4,Creturned by grandson in 80-year promise
OL,6,FHe had always intended to return the
OL,7,Fsand, to honour those he lost and in
OL,8,Fthanks for his life, but he was never
OL,9,Fable to.
OL,11,FInstead his grandson and former
OL,12,Fsoldier Dan Searson, from Manchester,
OL,13,Fpromised to do it on his behalf - and
OL,14,Fat dawn on the 80th anniversary of the
OL,15,Finvasion he returned the sand to its
OL,16,Frightful place.
