OL,3,CSand collected from D-Day beach
OL,4,Creturned by grandson in 80-year promise
OL,6,F"Having served myself I look at the
OL,7,Fbeaches and I can imagine the
OL,8,Fobstacles, the barbed wire, the blood,
OL,9,Fthe machine gun fire, people on their
OL,10,Fstomachs crawling up this beach in
OL,11,Forder to liberate not only France, but
OL,12,Fthe UK, absolutely phenomenal," he
OL,13,Fsaid.
OL,15,FTony Hulton, Chief Executive of
OL,16,FWalking With The Wounded, said:
OL,17,F"Events like this help us to connect
OL,18,Fveterans, service and communities and
OL,19,Fjust to remind others of the
OL,20,Fsacrifices that have been made for us."
